onsequences under globalization. Wang's findings will be of interest to scholars, practitioners, and concerned citizens hoping to deepen their understanding of globalization as well as useful for undergraduate and graduate courses in international relations, international and comparative political economy, and globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 4aBusiness and Economics : Business and Government. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economy and Society. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Economy. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849380040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493800423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493800/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles